associatefirewallrulegroup.name: AssociateFirewallRuleGroup
associatefirewallrulegroup.description: Grants permission to associate an Amazon VPC with a specified firewall rule group

associateresolverquerylogconfig.name: AssociateResolverQueryLogConfig
associateresolverquerylogconfig.description: Grants permission to associate an Amazon VPC with a specified query logging configuration

associateresolverrule.name: AssociateResolverRule
associateresolverrule.description: Grants permission to associate a specified Resolver rule with a specified VPC

createfirewalldomainlist.name: CreateFirewallDomainList
createfirewalldomainlist.description: Grants permission to create a Firewall domain list

createfirewallrule.name: CreateFirewallRule
createfirewallrule.description: Grants permission to create a Firewall rule within a Firewall rule group

createfirewallrulegroup.name: CreateFirewallRuleGroup
createfirewallrulegroup.description: Grants permission to create a Firewall rule group

createoutpostresolver.name: CreateOutpostResolver
createoutpostresolver.description: Grants permission to create a Route 53 Resolver on Outposts

createresolverendpoint.name: CreateResolverEndpoint
createresolverendpoint.description: Grants permission to create a Resolver endpoint. There are two types of Resolver endpoints, inbound and outbound

createresolverquerylogconfig.name: CreateResolverQueryLogConfig
createresolverquerylogconfig.description: Grants permission to create a Resolver query logging configuration, which defines where you want Resolver to save DNS query logs that originate in your VPCs

createresolverrule.name: CreateResolverRule
createresolverrule.description: Grants permission to define how to route queries originating from your VPC out of the VPC

deletefirewalldomainlist.name: DeleteFirewallDomainList
deletefirewalldomainlist.description: Grants permission to delete a Firewall domain list

deletefirewallrule.name: DeleteFirewallRule
deletefirewallrule.description: Grants permission to delete a Firewall rule within a Firewall rule group

deletefirewallrulegroup.name: DeleteFirewallRuleGroup
deletefirewallrulegroup.description: Grants permission to delete a Firewall rule group

deleteoutpostresolver.name: DeleteOutpostResolver
deleteoutpostresolver.description: Grants permission to delete a Route 53 Resolver on Outposts

deleteresolverendpoint.name: DeleteResolverEndpoint
deleteresolverendpoint.description: Grants permission to delete a Resolver endpoint. The effect of deleting a Resolver endpoint depends on whether it's an inbound or an outbound endpoint

deleteresolverquerylogconfig.name: DeleteResolverQueryLogConfig
deleteresolverquerylogconfig.description: Grants permission to delete a Resolver query logging configuration

deleteresolverrule.name: DeleteResolverRule
deleteresolverrule.description: Grants permission to delete a Resolver rule

disassociatefirewallrulegroup.name: DisassociateFirewallRuleGroup
disassociatefirewallrulegroup.description: Grants permission to remove the association between a specified Firewall rule group and a specified VPC

disassociateresolverendpointipaddress.name: DisassociateResolverEndpointIpAddress
disassociateresolverendpointipaddress.description: Grants permission to remove a specified IP address from a Resolver endpoint. This is an IP address that DNS queries pass through on the way to your network (outbound) or your VPCs (inbound)

disassociateresolverquerylogconfig.name: DisassociateResolverQueryLogConfig
disassociateresolverquerylogconfig.description: Grants permission to remove the association between a specified Resolver query logging configuration and a specified VPC

disassociateresolverrule.name: DisassociateResolverRule
disassociateresolverrule.description: Grants permission to remove the association between a specified Resolver rule and a specified VPC

getfirewallconfig.name: GetFirewallConfig
getfirewallconfig.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Firewall config

getfirewalldomainlist.name: GetFirewallDomainList
getfirewalldomainlist.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Firewall domain list

getfirewallrulegroup.name: GetFirewallRuleGroup
getfirewallrulegroup.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Firewall rule group

getfirewallrulegroupassociation.name: GetFirewallRuleGroupAssociation
getfirewallrulegroupassociation.description: Grants permission to get information about an association between a specified Firewall rule group and a VPC

getfirewallrulegrouppolicy.name: GetFirewallRuleGroupPolicy
getfirewallrulegrouppolicy.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Firewall rule group policy, which specifies the Firewall rule group operations and resources that you want to allow another AWS account to use

getoutpostresolver.name: GetOutpostResolver
getoutpostresolver.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Route 53 Resolver on Outposts

getresolverconfig.name: GetResolverConfig
getresolverconfig.description: Grants permission to get the Resolver Config status within the specified resource

getresolverdnssecconfig.name: GetResolverDnssecConfig
getresolverdnssecconfig.description: Grants permission to get the DNSSEC validation support status for DNS queries within the specified resource

getresolverendpoint.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Resolver endpoint, such as whether it's an inbound or an outbound endpoint, and the IP addresses in your VPC that DNS queries are forwarded to on the way into or out of your VPC

getresolverquerylogconfigassociation.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified association between a Resolver query logging configuration and an Amazon VPC. When you associate a VPC with a query logging configuration, Resolver logs DNS queries that originate in that VPC

getresolverquerylogconfigpolicy.description: Grants permission to get information about a specified Resolver query logging policy, which specifies the Resolver query logging operations and resources that you want to allow another AWS account to use

getresolverrulepolicy.name: GetResolverRulePolicy

importfirewalldomains.name: ImportFirewallDomains
importfirewalldomains.description: Grants permission to add, remove or replace Firewall domains in a Firewall domain list

listfirewallconfigs.name: ListFirewallConfigs
listfirewallconfigs.description: Grants permission to list all the Firewall config that current AWS account is able to check

listresolverconfigs.name: ListResolverConfigs
listresolverconfigs.description: Grants permission to list Resolver Config statuses

listresolverdnssecconfigs.name: ListResolverDnssecConfigs
listresolverdnssecconfigs.description: Grants permission to list the DNSSEC validation support status for DNS queries

listresolverendpointipaddresses.name: ListResolverEndpointIpAddresses

listresolverendpoints.name: ListResolverEndpoints
listresolverendpoints.description: Grants permission to list all the Resolver endpoints that were created using the current AWS account

listresolverquerylogconfigassociations.name: ListResolverQueryLogConfigAssociations
listresolverquerylogconfigassociations.description: Grants permission to list information about associations between Amazon VPCs and query logging configurations

listresolverquerylogconfigs.description: Grants permission to list information about the specified query logging configurations, which define where you want Resolver to save DNS query logs and specify the VPCs that you want to log queries for

listresolverrules.name: ListResolverRules

putresolverquerylogconfigpolicy.name: PutResolverQueryLogConfigPolicy
putresolverquerylogconfigpolicy.description: Grants permission to specify an AWS account that you want to share a query logging configuration with, the query logging configuration that you want to share, and the operations that you want the account to be able to perform on the configuration

updatefirewalldomains.name: UpdateFirewallDomains
